@startuml seq-history
'' PlantUML over Mermaid because navigation history is an ordered handshake where a pure app-db index move
'' drives a DataScript-backed body swap; the activation lifetimes and the :ds/rev recompute hop matter, so
'' PlantUML sequence (autonumber + activation + concept colour) is the right tool. Literal palette hexes:
'' teal #2D9574 view, blue #4F97D7 re-frame, blue-violet #7590DB app-db history, purple #A45BAD DataScript.
!include _vv-theme.iuml

title Navigation history — Alt+← (Back) ⟶ body swap (Command replay)\n:ui/history {:stack :idx}

autonumber "<b>[0]"

actor User #9F8766
participant "toolbar /\nkeybindings" as UI #2D9574
participant ":history/back\n(reg-event-db)" as RF #4F97D7
collections "app-db\n:ui/history" as DB #7590DB
participant ":doc/active\nsubscription" as SUB #7590DB
database "DataScript\nconn" as DS #A45BAD
participant "views\nmarkdown-body" as V #2D9574

== guard ==
User -> UI : Alt+←  (or click ←)
UI -> RF : [:history/back]
activate RF
RF -> DB : read {:stack :idx}
alt idx > 0  (can go back)
  RF -> DB : :idx ← (dec idx)\n:active-path ← (get stack (dec idx))
  note right of DB
    History is a Command stack: each visited path is a
    reified entry. Back/forward just move :idx; the stack
    itself is unchanged (no re-navigation side effects).
  end note
else idx = 0  (at oldest)
  RF -> RF : no-op (history/can-back? = false\n→ ← button disabled)
end
deactivate RF

== recompute + swap ==
DB --> SUB : :ui/active-path changed →\n:doc/active sub re-runs (:<- [:ui/active-path])
activate SUB
SUB -> DS : ds/active-doc @conn for new path\n(pull :doc/path :doc/kind :doc/html :doc/error)
activate DS
DS --> SUB : the prior document entity (already open)
deactivate DS
SUB --> V : new :doc/html
deactivate SUB
activate V
V -> V : component-did-update →\nset! innerHTML html
deactivate V

note over SUB, DS #FFF6D6
  Back/forward never re-read the file or re-render Markdown:
  the target doc is already a :doc entity in DataScript, so
  switching is a pure index move + a sub recompute. Forward
  (Alt+→) is the mirror: idx < count-1 → (inc idx).
end note

legend right
  |= Colour |= Participant / concept |
  |<#9F8766>| User |
  |<#2D9574>| view (toolbar, body) |
  |<#4F97D7>| re-frame event (:history/back) |
  |<#7590DB>| app-db :ui/history (Command stack + idx) |
  |<#A45BAD>| DataScript (the already-open :doc entity) |
endlegend
@enduml
